g.title: j1085918167
g.text: Can I ask you a... potentially strange question?

g.title: j3719181797
g.text: You've been poisoning it, haven't you?!

g.title: j1951657800
g.text: You wish. No getting out that easy.

g.title: j3008190056
g.text: I'm curious why you cut it up into... perfect squares. Even the pizza.

g.title: j4037546121
g.text: Honestly? It kind of reminds me of... I don't know.

g.title: j3324308053
g.text: Force of habit. That's how the rations were served on the Zariman, the ship that got stuck in the void.

g.title: j1885135793
g.text: The only home I've had where I wasn't alone.

g.title: j1973814955
g.text: Actually, sorry. I don't want to talk about it. [End.]

g.title: j4030915177
g.text: When it wasn't just me, myself, and my cubed food rations.

g.title: j4250063916
g.text: Well, I guess I could try making square spaghetti if you want.

g.title: j1948902429
g.text: So. I guess I do it because there's comfort in it.

g.title: j3102929110
g.text: I'll tell you what. If you make it, I'll eat it.

g.title: j3965661999
g.text: I know how you feel. Routines can help you feel grounded, especially when everything's gone to shit.

g.title: j3265159834
g.text: I tell you what - I make a mean cubed omelette.

g.title: Chat ends. Next chat will be ArthurSpaghetti.
g.text: Chat ends. Next chat will be ArthurSpaghetti.
